    <text id="B1191T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Jackson receives notice of his appointment as Bureau Agent (presumably for his
                    transfer out of Augusta County).</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <abbr expan="Bureau of Refugees, Freedmen and Abandoned Lands">Bur. R.F. and
                        A.L.</abbr><lb/><abbr expan="Headquarters">HdQrs</abbr>
                    <abbr expan="Assistant Commissioner">Asst. Comr</abbr>, <abbr expan="Virginia"
                        >Va</abbr>
                    <name type="recipient">Jackson, Thos. P.<lb/>Agent, <abbr
                            expan="Bureau of Refugees, Freedmen and Abandoned Lands">Bur. R.F. and
                            A.L.</abbr>
                        <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr></name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1868-03-24">March 24th 1868</date>
                        <name type="place">Richmond, Va.</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Sir, </salute>
                </opener>

                <p>I enclose herewith your appointment as Agent of this Bureau. The accompanying
                    oath after being duly executed will be returned to these Head Quarters.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>By order of <abbr expan="Brevet Brigadier General">Bvt. Brig. Genl.</abbr>
                        <hi rend="underline">O. Brown</hi>, <abbr expan="United States Volunteers"
                            >U.S.V.</abbr>
                        <abbr expan="Assistant Commissioner">Asst. Comr.</abbr></salute>
                    <signed>Will A. Coulter<lb/><abbr expan="Brevet Captain">Bvt. Capt.</abbr>
                        <abbr expan="United States Army">U.S.A.</abbr>
                        <abbr expan="Acting Assistant Adjutant General">A.A.A.Genl.</abbr></signed>
                    <seg type="postscript">(2 enclosures)</seg>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
